And when it comes to training workload in AI, we have inference and training, and training workloads add one more challenge: there's only one single job running across the whole infrastructure. So, as Brian was mentioning, if even one single machine has some issue, how do we monitor that? The whole workload is going to be impacted. Prediction and correlation are important, because if there is an issue somewhere in the machine, maybe it is detected somewhere else, because somebody else was requesting that memory read—the concept of RDMA, remote direct memory access. So the machine that detects the problem, the problem might actually be somewhere else. How do we figure that out? It's not easy. So we're running into that challenge as well.

