And finally, what do we want to see in the future? Today we have legacy hardware management. The rack manager that we use today in the rack is primarily to manage the liquid cooling—that's the primary use case for us right now—and we need to expand beyond that. Where we want to go is to have more analysis and predictive techniques implemented in the rack manager, and a lot of this intelligent management and automation, so that self-contained infrastructure can manage the events, and from a deployment point of view: a machine is failing, predict it; before the machine fails, take the machine out of the cluster, migrate the workload, take the machine down, go through repair—auto-repair. As much automation as we can build in is what we need here.

